Epigyne as illustrated (
Fig. 2
), with quadrate convex hairy plate; plate with pronounced, nearly triangular atrium anteriorly, copulatory openings concealed at lateral margins of atrium. Vulva (
Fig. 3
) with very short copulatory ducts connected with copulatory openings and spermathecae; spermathecae posteriorly nearly ballshaped, touching at midline, each with tube-shaped apophysis laterally.

Male palp (
Figs 5–6
) with retrolateral patellar apophysis long, hooked at distal end, with bifid retrolateral tibial apophysis, distal parts of upper and lower branches crossing each other. Embolus long, originating prolaterally, median part hidden behind membranous conductor (
Fig. 5
). Conductor small, distally. Median apophysis large, apex pointing retrolaterally, sclerotized.
